    "body": "From the top of my head, you should be able to give `fully.qualified.name.of.the.test.module[:which_test_in_it]`\r\n\r\n```\r\niptest IPython.core.tests.test_iplib:doctest_tb_verbose\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe for convenience when you want to run a full test suite from a module you can also give the \"path\" (ie qualified named with `.` replace with `/`. I use it like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncd ~; iptest IPython/core/tests/test_iplib.py ; cd -\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich make it relatively convenient for tab completion, so the argument is not really a \"path\" and `.py` is stripped.\r\n\r\nWe could probably indeed add that to Contributing.md. \r\n\r\n@meeseeksdev tag \"good first issue\""
